The President made opening remarks at a meeting focused on investing together and investing stronger in the G20. He highlighted the Partnership for Global Infrastructure and Investment, which aims to mobilize $600 billion over five years for infrastructure and investments in low- and middle-income countries. He mentioned collaborations in climate, energy security, digital connectivity, health infrastructure, and gender equity. Specific projects include the Just Energy Transition Partnership with Indonesia and Japan, investments in renewable energy and climate-resilient transportation in Indonesia, investments in critical minerals and technology for clean energy transition, efforts to improve digital connectivity in Papua New Guinea and Liberia, support for vaccine manufacturing and health infrastructure in Africa and Asia, and initiatives for gender equity and childcare. The President emphasized the importance of these investments for creating opportunity, equality, and a more secure and prosperous world. He invited others to join this partnership.